NAME
    stat - display file status

SYNOPSIS
    stat [options] <file...>

DESCRIPTION
    Displays detailed information about files including size,
    permissions, timestamps, and type.

OPTIONS
    -L              Follow symbolic links
    -f              Display filesystem information
    -c <format>     Use custom format string
    -t              Terse output (single line)

FORMAT SEQUENCES
    %n              File name
    %N              Quoted name with symlink target
    %s              Size in bytes
    %b              Blocks allocated
    %f              Raw mode in hexadecimal
    %a              Access rights in octal
    %A              Access rights human readable
    %u              User ID of owner
    %U              User name of owner
    %g              Group ID of owner
    %G              Group name of owner
    %h              Number of hard links
    %i              Inode number
    %F              File type description
    %X              Access time (seconds since epoch)
    %x              Access time (human readable)
    %Y              Modification time (seconds since epoch)
    %y              Modification time (human readable)
    %Z              Change time (seconds since epoch)
    %z              Change time (human readable)

DEFAULT OUTPUT
    File: filename
    Size: bytes     Blocks: n       file type
    Access: (mode/perms)  Uid: (n/name)  Gid: (n/name)
    Access: timestamp
    Modify: timestamp
    Change: timestamp

EXAMPLES
    stat file.txt
        Display full status information

    stat -L symlink
        Follow symlink and show target's status

    stat -c "%n: %s bytes" *
        Custom format: name and size

    stat -c "%A %n" /api/data/*
        Show permissions and names

    stat -t *.json
        Terse output for all JSON files

    stat -c "%y" file
        Just show modification time

    stat -c "%a %n" /tmp/*
        Show octal permissions

EXIT STATUS
    0       Success
    1       Error (file not found, etc.)

SEE ALSO
    ls, file, find
